<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='669000' id='t-669000'>things like grades, SAT's, degrees,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='672000' id='t-672000'>the number of years in schooling.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='674000' id='t-674000'>What it really takes to do well, to lead a meaningful life,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='677000' id='t-677000'>are things that are deeper,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='679000' id='t-679000'>things we don't really even have words for.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='682000' id='t-682000'>And so let me list just a couple of the things</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='684000' id='t-684000'>I think this research points us toward trying to understand.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
